The paper presents a deep learning-based approach for segmentation of axon and myelin from microscopy images of the nervous system. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for segmentation also suggests relevance to neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of morphological metrics, which could relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of extracting quantitative information from images.
